Derry Mathews' world title challenge is in limbo after Richar Abril withdrew for a second time. A statement from the 31-year-old's promoter read: 'We have been made aware of Abril's withdrawal and are in discussions with the World Boxing Association and representatives of Richar Abril as to the current position of the world title as this is the second time he has withdrawn from this fight with less than two weeks before fight night.